quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,82,"And who I aspire that He will forgive me my sin on the Day of Recompense."
  26,83,"[And he said], "
  26,84,"And grant me a mention [i.e., reputation] of honor among later generations."
  27,55,"Do you indeed approach men with desire instead of women? Rather, you are a people behaving ignorantly."
  27,56,"But the answer of his people was not except that they said, "
  27,57,"So We saved him and his family, except for his wife; We destined her to be of those who remained behind."
  28,28,"[Moses] said, "
  28,29,"And when Moses had completed the term and was traveling with his family, he perceived from the direction of the mount a fire. He said to his family, "
  28,30,"But when he came to it, he was called from the right side of the valley in a blessed spot - from the tree,{1} ",footnotes:1:Which was within the fire.